{"title_page": "A Paris Education", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = A Paris Education\n| image          = A Paris Education.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jean-Paul Civeyrac]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Jean Paul Civeyrac\n| starring       = [[Andranic Manet]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2018|2|18|[[68th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin]]|2018|4|18|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 127 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''A Paris Education''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Mes provinciales'''}}) is a 2018 French [[drama film]] directed by [[Jean-Paul Civeyrac]]. It was screened in the Panorama section at the [[68th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Pan2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41492.html |title=Programme for Berlinale Panorama 2018 Complete: What\u2019s Your Poison? |work=Berlinale |date=25 January 2018 |accessdate=29 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129195656/https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41492.html |archive-date=29 January 2018 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Andranic Manet]] as Etienne\n* [[Diane Rouxel]] as Lucie\n* [[Jenna Thiam]] as Valentina\n* [[Gonzague Van Bervesseles]] as Jean-No\u00ebl\n* [[Corentin Fila]] as Mathias\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|6593240|A Paris Education}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Paris Education, A}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2018 drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n{{2010s-France-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = A Paris Education\n| image          = A Paris Education.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jean-Paul Civeyrac]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Jean Paul Civeyrac\n| starring       = [[Andranic Manet]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2018|2|18|[[68th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin]]|2018|4|18|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 127 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''A Paris Education''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Mes provinciales'''}}) is a 2018 French [[drama film]] directed by [[Jean-Paul Civeyrac]]. It was screened in the Panorama section at the [[68th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Pan2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41492.html |title=Programme for Berlinale Panorama 2018 Complete: What\u2019s Your Poison? |work=Berlinale |date=25 January 2018 |accessdate=29 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129195656/https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41492.html |archive-date=29 January 2018 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Andranic Manet]] as Etienne\n* [[Diane Rouxel]] as Lucie\n* [[Jenna Thiam]] as Valentina\n* [[Gonzague Van Bervesseles]] as Jean-No\u00ebl\n* [[Corentin Fila]] as Mathias\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|6593240|A Paris Education}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Paris Education, A}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2018 drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n{{2010s-France-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Paris_Education"}
{"title_page": "Lux \u00c6terna (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lux \u00c6terna\n| image          = Lux \u00c6terna.jpg\n| caption        = Cannes poster\n| director       = [[Gaspar No\u00e9]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Gaspar No\u00e9\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Charlotte Gainsbourg]]\n* [[B\u00e9atrice Dalle]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[Beno\u00eet Debie]]\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2019|5|18|[[2019 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 50 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n}}\n\n'''''Lux \u00c6terna''''' is a 2019 French [[drama film]] directed by [[Gaspar No\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.festival-cannes.com/en/press/press-articles/communique/articles/the-screenings-guide-2019|title=The Screenings Guide 2019|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref> It was screened out of competition at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/apr/18/cannes-festival-2019-full-list-of-films |title=Cannes festival 2019: full list of films |work=The Guardian |accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref> It is a [[metafictional]] drama centered around Gainsbourg and Dalle playing themselves making a film about [[witches]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Charlotte Gainsbourg]] as Charlotte\n* [[B\u00e9atrice Dalle]] as B\u00e9atrice\n* [[Mica Arga\u00f1araz]] as Mica\n* [[Karl Glusman]] as Karl\n* [[Abbey Lee]] as Abbey\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n[[Review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]] calculated a 60% approval from 10 reviews and scored a 5.57/10 average rating.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lux_aeterna|title=Lux \u00c6terna|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|access-date=26 May 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] assigned the film a score of 58 out of 100 based on 5 reviews, signifying \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/lux-aeterna |title=Lux \u00c6terna Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|10272534|Lux \u00c6terna}}\n\n{{Gaspar No\u00e9}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lux Aeterna}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Gaspar No\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n{{2010s-France-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Lux \u00c6terna\n| image          = Lux \u00c6terna.jpg\n| caption        = Cannes poster\n| director       = [[Gaspar No\u00e9]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Gaspar No\u00e9\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Charlotte Gainsbourg]]\n* [[B\u00e9atrice Dalle]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[Beno\u00eet Debie]]\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2019|5|18|[[2019 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 50 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n}}\n\n'''''Lux \u00c6terna''''' is a 2019 French [[drama film]] directed by [[Gaspar No\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.festival-cannes.com/en/press/press-articles/communique/articles/the-screenings-guide-2019|title=The Screenings Guide 2019|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref> It was screened out of competition at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/apr/18/cannes-festival-2019-full-list-of-films |title=Cannes festival 2019: full list of films |work=The Guardian |accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>. It is a [[metafictional]] drama centered around Gainsbourg and Dalle playing themselves making a film about [[witches]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Charlotte Gainsbourg]] as Charlotte\n* [[B\u00e9atrice Dalle]] as B\u00e9atrice\n* [[Mica Arga\u00f1araz]] as Mica\n* [[Karl Glusman]] as Karl\n* [[Abbey Lee]] as Abbey\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n[[Review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]] calculated a 60% approval from 10 reviews and scored a 5.57/10 average rating.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lux_aeterna|title=Lux \u00c6terna|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|access-date=26 May 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] assigned the film a score of 58 out of 100 based on 5 reviews, signifying \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/lux-aeterna |title=Lux \u00c6terna Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|10272534|Lux \u00c6terna}}\n\n{{Gaspar No\u00e9}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lux Aeterna}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Gaspar No\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n{{2010s-France-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Sebastian James", "label": "safe", "comment": "+", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lux_%C3%86terna_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Our Father (2016 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2016 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Our Father\n| image          = Avinu.jpg \n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Meni Yaesh]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Meni Yaesh\n| starring       = [[Moris Cohen]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography =[[Ram Shweky]] \n| editing        =[[Shira Arad]] \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2016|6|5|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 90 minutes\n| country        = Israel\n| language       = Hebrew\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Our Father''''' ({{lang-he|'''Avinu'''}}) is a 2016 Israeli [[drama film]] directed by [[Meni Yaesh]]. It was one of five films nominated for the Best Film Award at the [[Ophir Award]]s.<ref name=\"Israel\">{{cite web|url=http://www.israelfilmacademy.co.il/?item=17279&section=595 |title= \u05d4\u05d4\u05db\u05e8\u05d6\u05d4 \u05e2\u05dc \u05d4\u05e2\u05d5\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd \u05dc\u05d2\u05de\u05e8 - \u05e4\u05e8\u05e1\u05d9 \u05d0\u05d5\u05e4\u05d9\u05e8 2016 |work=Israel Film Academy|date=10 August 2016 |accessdate=10 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"JP\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Culture/2016-Ophir-nominations-announced-snubs-and-all-464603 |title=2016 Ophir nominations announced \u2013 snubs and all  |first=Hannah| last=Brown |work=[[The Jerusalem Post]] |date=20 August 2016 |accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Moris Cohen]] as Ovadia Rachamim\n* [[Rotem Zissman-Cohen]] as Rachel Rachmim \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4466358|Our Father}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Our Father}}\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:2016 drama films]]\n[[Category:Israeli films]]\n[[Category:Israeli drama films]]\n[[Category:Hebrew-language films]]\n{{Israel-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2016 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n|